<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_2de6a5ba-3245-4fd0-a45d-a4a583bb6293" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>J1F1</sptc><title id="_4551441f-084b-4ed4-abf2-774e7a9c66da">Energy efficiency</title><archive-num/><subclause id="_f3e62b3d-012f-4c68-8114-027bfc8b591d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_4713d696-7967-4112-9ad5-f6c3a1687dfe">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A building must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_e5e1e5ad-35f3-49d3-957f-99d58316416b">reduce the energy consumption and energy peak demand of key energy using equipment; and</li><li id="_d41e8c67-08a8-4db1-a44f-6538d01c3cb6">reduce the greenhouse gas emissions that occur as a result of a building’s energy consumption and energy source; and</li><li id="_d2d8f280-26a4-4df5-a466-74e65b1e872e">for a Class 4 part of a building, improve occupant health and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1186_0.6.0.xml#_83c1f020-a2d5-4bf0-a87e-b8fa76ac96c3" id="_19f5f563-a55a-485e-96d8-13bc9cdbe120" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">amenity</xref> by mitigating the impact of extreme hot and cold weather events and energy blackouts; and</li><li id="_aad751e5-c531-470c-97a7-c9d967b8b4cc">for other than in a Class 4 part of a building, protect occupant health and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1186_0.6.0.xml#_83c1f020-a2d5-4bf0-a87e-b8fa76ac96c3" id="_37726a93-ecb3-4f8d-9b19-6bca6363cefd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">amenity</xref> by ensuring the building <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1259_5.7.0.xml#_71ea06f9-79ec-4eae-bdf4-d90302f51eb5" id="_e4ce96fe-4211-42db-bae4-2bb27cb05a5d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">envelope</xref> assists in the maintenance of acceptable internal conditions while the building is occupied; and</li><li id="_e57a046f-c306-4a16-9c34-7dabba930c08">be able to accommodate the installation of distributed energy resources.</li></ol></subclause></clause>